<section class="tension" id="how-it-works">
<div class="section-inner">
<div class="section-eyebrow">The problem</div>
<h2>Many job evaluation systems were built for a different world.</h2>
<div class="tension-grid">
<div class="tension-left">
<p>A world of fixed roles and stable structures isn't how modern organisations operate. Roles evolve, structures shift, and governance expectations keep rising.</p>
<p>Engage was built for the way organisations work now — structured methodology with practical usability, so you grade roles with more confidence and less friction.</p>
</div>
<div class="tension-right">
<div class="pain-label">Many job evaluation systems are still:</div>
<ul class="pain-list">
<li>Slow to implement and difficult to explain</li>
<li>Dependent on outdated job descriptions</li>
<li>Hard to maintain as roles evolve</li>
<li>Opaque — a black box that erodes trust</li>
<li>Highly reliant on expensive external consultants</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
